# Performance and reliability

- Avoid N+1 queries: batch or join in repository when listing related data.
- Redis: use TTL on revocation keys; prefer pipelines for multiple reads in hot paths.
- Timeouts: respect DB/driver defaults; document long-running jobs if added later.
- Do not block the event loop with CPU-heavy work in request handlers.
